You can [conditionally exclude fields][1] by using [REMOVE][2] in aggregation. In your case, it should be:

    Conversation.aggregate([
      {$match: {&quot;users.user&quot;: id}},
      {
         $project: {
           title: 1,
           type: 1,
           users: {
             $cond: { 
               if: { $eq: [ &quot;$type&quot;, &quot;private&quot; ] }, 
               then: &quot;$users&quot;, 
               else: &quot;$$REMOVE&quot; 
             }
           }
         }
      }
    ])

*Side note*: If you specify only a single &lt;query&gt; condition in the `$elemMatch` expression, you do not need to use `$elemMatch`.
  [1]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/project/#remove-example
  [2]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/aggregation-variables/#variable.REMOVE

