I see that you have to build your widget from the output of two futures. You can either use two `FutureBuilders` or have helper method to combine them into one and simplify code.  

Also never compute/invoke async function from `build` function. It has to be initialized before (either in constructor or `initState` method), other wise widget might end up repainting for ever.  

Coming to solution, to simplify code, its better to combine both future outputs into single class like below:


Data required for `build` method:
```

class DataRequiredForBuild {
  String imagesPath;
  List items;

  DataRequiredForBuild({
    this.imagesPath,
    this.items,
  });
}
```

Function to fetch all required data:

```

Future&lt;DataRequiredForBuild&gt; _fetchAllData() async {
  return DataRequiredForBuild(
    imagesPath: await getImagesPath(),
    items: await databaseHelperGetList(),
  );
}
```


Now putting everything together in Widget:

```
Future&lt;DataRequiredForBuild&gt; _dataRequiredForBuild;

@override
void initState() {
  super.initState();
  // this should not be done in build method
  _dataRequiredForBuild = _fetchAllData();
}

@override
Widget build(BuildContext context) {
  return Scaffold(
    //removed
    body: FutureBuilder&lt;DataRequiredForBuild&gt;(
      future: _dataRequiredForBuild,
      builder: (context, snapshot) {
        return snapshot.hasData
            ? ListView.builder(
                itemCount: snapshot.data.items.length,
                itemBuilder: (_, int position) {
                  final item = snapshot.data.items[position];
                  final image = &quot;${snapshot.data.imagesPath}/${item.row[0]}.jpg&quot;;
                  return Card(
                      child: ListTile(
                    leading: Image.asset(image),
                    title: Text(item.row[1]),
                    subtitle: Text(item.row[2]),
                    trailing: Icon(Icons.launch),
                  ));
                })
            : Center(
                child: CircularProgressIndicator(),
              );
      },
    ),
  );
}

```

